race.description: Walsh Frames And Trusses Maiden Plate
race.comment: EXILED PRINCE (3) stuck on well when resuming last start to finish third over 1175m at Albury after showing good early speed. Strips fitter and gets in light with the 3kg claimer engaged. Bold showing anticipated. SKELDALE HOUSE (4) is a Trapeze Artist gelding on debut for the Ponsonby yard. Fitter for a recent Hawkesbury trial. Looks set for a bright start. SMOLENSKI (5) has been finding the line nicely and should relish the rise in trip. Gets a key booking in Heywood and is ready to put it all together. DELAGO SERG (1) has been in the money five times but couldn't add to the tally when fresh from a spell last start. Led into the straight ion that occasion but tired late at Queanbeyan. Should take a lot from that last outing. ICED POPPY (10) has left herself with too much to do in her first two outings. Can give this a shake if she takes closer order under the light weight.
